==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: manila paper
<hw>manila paper</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A durable brown or buff paper
or thin cardboard with a smooth light brown finish, made of Manila hemp,
and used as a wrapping paper, or as a cheap printing and writing paper.
The name is also given to inferior papers, made of other
fiber.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> manila, manila paper, manilla, manilla
paper.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manila tamarind</ent>⟦br⟧
